</div></div><header><div class="vine-p p-content_ArticleInfo"></div><h1 class="gl_headline">Chart: National debt, by president</h1><div class="article_details clearfix"><div class="byline">By <a href="http://maddowblog.msnbc.msn.com/_nv/more/section/archive?author=MaddowShow">The Rachel Maddow Show</a></div><div> &nbsp;-&nbsp; </div><div class="dateline">Mon Sep 20, 2010 4:14 PM EDT</div></div></header><div class="postBody"><div class="postText"><div class="vine-p p-content_ArticleText "><div class="articleText"><p><img src="http://msnbcmedia.msn.com/i/MSNBC/Sections/TVNews/MSNBC%20TV/Maddow/Blog/2010/09/debt.jpg" /></p>
<p>Rick Seaman of Portland, Oregon, made this chart from data he found on <a href="http://www.treasurydirect.gov/govt/reports/pd/mspd/mspd.htm">TreasuryDirect.gov</a>.</p>
<p> "If voters don't understand this, the media has failed them," Seaman writes.</p>
<p>[<a href="http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/27891950/">Send more stuff, please</a>.]</p></div></div></div></div>












